Quote:  Unfortunately, cages also prevent the native pollinators such as pekapeka, the short-tailed bat, and as yet other unknown reptile or bird propagators from reaching the flowers. As a consequence, every April/May season the so-called "flowers of Hades" must be laboriously hand-pollinated.
